        <p class="lead text-justify">Due to a bug in Stravas API (We are hoping for a fix soon) there is something you
          should know. When we read the leaderboards
          the riders names we get back are now abbrivated to their first name followed by the first letter of their
          surname (e.g John Doe = John D). This poses an
          issue for us recognising club members who have the same first name and first letter of their surname which
          confuses our points system. An example would be
          John Davies, John Dunn and John Doe all showing as John D on the leaderboard with a cumulative points
          tally.<br><br>

          <strong>How to fix this?</strong><br><br>

          After some trial we believe the best way to solve this temporary issue without completely changing the name of
          members with confilicting names (If only it was so easy) is to ask members to ensure their name is unique in
          some way by doing the following:
          <ol>
            <li class="lead">Add a club abbreviation after your first name and leave surname as it is: John BCC Doe.
            </li>
            <li class="lead">Add a club abbreviation before your first name and leave surname as it is: BCC John Doe.
            </li>
            <li class="lead">Add an emoji before or after your first name and leave surname as it is: 🚴John Doe.</li>
          </ol>
          <p class="lead">I do apologise if this does apply to your club and we hope the issue will be resolved quickly!
            If
            there is any issues appear please contact us.</p>
        </p><br><br>
      </section>

